area_descr.1: This small area, situated near railroad shops and industrial development is old and contains a very poor security. It is occupied entirely by working people.
This is an old section of Phoenix, adjacent to the business and industrial sections of the city, occupied entirely by a poor class of working people. The security is ragged.
This section, adjoining the railroad station and yards, is a semi-industrial section, with very poor houses. Negroes, Mexicans and different classes of foreigners are rapidly occupying this area.
This section, lying outside the city limits, is very ragged, occupied by Mexicans, Negroes and the low class of white people. There is no sale for property herein.
